          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_ContractUpdate",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to update contract details in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.Contract",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table within a Microsoft SQL Server database. It takes various parameters related to contract information, updates the corresponding record, and logs the operation's outcome. The procedure includes error handling and logging mechanisms to ensure that any issues during the update process are captured and reported."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
